Create returns a JavaDownloadToken body plus
opc-work-request-id, while update and delete
return work-request headers only. The reviewed
runtime resumes all three phases through
GetWorkRequest before rereading
GetJavaDownloadToken.
The token value authorizes downloads and is
intentionally excluded from published status,
generated docs, and generic bind/parity matching
in this story. No Kubernetes Secret side effects
are emitted.
Pre-create reuse stays bounded to exact
compartmentId plus displayName matching and does
not use the sensitive value filter even though
ListJavaDownloadTokens supports it.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the delete work
request is terminal and GetJavaDownloadToken or
fallback ListJavaDownloadTokens confirms the
token is gone.
end note
